latestPosts.caption:
let’s talk about how you can get this Cherry Cock shade by @birdsofparadyes to actually turn out like mine 🍒

• I’ve had history with this colour first time I used it (last year), it came out wayyy too bright. Which didn’t look good on me and I literally had to wash my hair again and again just to tone it down 😩

• Cut to this time: I colored my hair again a few days back. Mixed in too much conditioner, thinking I was playing smart… but , the color didn’t even show. Like barely there 😬

• So yeah, I reapplied it again after a few days this time with just a tiny bit of conditioner (like those mini ₹1 sachet vibes). That’s when the magic happened 🙂

• Here’s how I made it work:
➤ Mix the color with very little conditioner (only if you want to tone it down a bit).
➤ Apply it evenly don’t rush it.
➤ After coloring, I used a color safe shampoo, then followed up with the @birdsofparadyes hair mask & conditioner.
➤ I finished with a colour protect serum to lock everything in.

🧴 Just a quick note  usually when you’re using the hair masks from @birdsofparadyes, you’d apply the mask before shampoo and then follow with conditioner. But since I already had colour on my hair, I shampooed first, then used the mask, and finished with conditioner. So yeah, do it based on your hair’s situation 🤓

Also since I coloured my hair, I try not to shampoo too often. Even the gentlest shampoos can strip a bit of colour, so I skip it when I can and focus on hydrating care instead 💧

✨ And this Cherry Cock shade hits so different in sunlight. Brighter, bolder, and seriously SO pretty when the light catches it 🔥

If you’re new to colouring, you can check out @birdsofparadyes’ website they’ve got hair care products that’ll help keep your color fresh and hair healthy. Trust me, it makes a difference 

And if you’ve been waiting to try bold hair but overthink every step… maybe this is your sign 🤍
You don’t have to get it perfect. Just try. Learn. And vibe in the color that makes you feel alive.
